    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Common soldiers' armor worn during the 15th and 16th centuries, typically sleeveless and of waist-length or slightly longer. One form had small overlapping iron or horn plates fixed inside between layers of fabric by trellis-pattern stitching. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000039541/Tarassuk and Blair, Complete Encyclopedia of Arms and Armor (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000004431/Blair, European Armour (1958)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Armadura de soldado ordinario usada durante los siglos XV y XVI. Consistente en una chaqueta de lona con unas pequeñas placas sobrepuestas de hierro o asta, fijadas en el interior entre capas de tejido mediante puntadas en forma de enrejado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Harnas van gewone soldaten, dat werd gedragen in de 15e en 16e eeuw, bestaande uit een canvas jack met kleine overlappende ijzeren of hoornen plaatjes die aan de binnenkant waren bevestigd tussen lagen van stof, door middel van stiksel in een rasterpatroon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西元十五與十六世紀時常見的士兵盔甲，由帆布短上衣和交疊的小型鐵片或獸角片所組成，鐵片係以格柵形縫法固定在布料夾層之間。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
